    <stitle>Side Mount Cooling Package - RE Bus - REMOVE AND INSTALL PROCEDURES - SURGE TANK</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="Remove and Install" graphiccount="3">
        <title>SURGE TANK</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Surge Tank - Removal</title>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>Prior to draining any coolant from the system, close two heater shut-off valves. The heater
                        shut-off valves can be accessed through the left-side rear compartment service door.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Unlatch and open the rear compartment service doors, left-side door, and rear door.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1202301" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg12/G1202301.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 4. Radiator Drain Valve</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. LEFT-SIDE RADIATOR FRAME</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. DRAIN VALVE</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The entire cooling system will not require draining to remove the surge tank. Only drain
                        enough coolant to empty the surge tank.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the radiator drain valve prior to removal of the surge tank. Place tray under the
                    radiator to collect coolant from radiator. Open the drain valve and drain coolant.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1202302" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg12/G1202302.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 5. Surge Tank Hoses</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. SURGE TANK</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. SURGE TANK HOSES</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <randlist type="bullet">
                        <item>
                            <para>Tag and mark hoses before removal to ensure proper installation.</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Cap and plug all hoses upon removal to stop leakage and prevent contamination.</para>
                        </item>
                    </randlist>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove four hoses from surge tank.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1202303" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg12/G1202303.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 6. Surge Tank Mounting</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. SURGE TANK</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. CABLE STRAPS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. MOUNT NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. JAM NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. MOUNT BRACKET</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two jam nuts, mount nuts, and washers from two cable straps.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove surge tank from mount brackets.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If replacement is needed, transfer all fittings to the new surge tank.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Surge Tank - Installation</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Check the surge tank prior to installation for any leaks and/or damage.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position surge tank on mount brackets (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1202303">Figure 6, Items 1 and 6</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position two cable straps on surge tank and install two washers, mount nuts, and jam
                    nuts on cable straps (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1202303">Figure 6</hotlnk>). Torque mount nuts to 21 to 27 lbf-ft (28 to 37 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install four surge tank hoses (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1202303">Figure 5</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Fill cooling system to proper level and leak test the cooling system. Special Tool
                    number
                    <emph type="bold">550500INT</emph>
                    is recommended to fill and leak test the cooling system.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>After filling the cooling system, open two heater shut-off valves and recheck the coolant
                        level. The heater shut-off valves can be accessed through the left-side rear compartment service
                        door.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Close and latch the rear compartment service doors, left-side door, and rear door.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
